A hands-on implementation of One-Hot Encoding using Pandas and Scikit-Learn. 
This project demonstrates multiple encoding techniques, including standard OHE, K-1 encoding,
and handling high-cardinality categorical features with top-category encoding for machine learning preprocessing.

# Key Features:
One-Hot Encoding using Pandas (get_dummies)
K-1 Dummy Variable Encoding
One-Hot Encoding using Scikit-Learn's OneHotEncoder
Train-Test Split implementation
Handling categorical variables for ML models
Top Category Encoding for high-cardinality features
Practical examples using a car dataset
